doc.after: The basic structure duties function and operations of the government of the state of Florida are defined and established by the Florida Constitution which establishes the basic law of the state and guarantees various rights and freedoms of the people The state government consists of three separate branches judicial executive and legislative The legislature enacts bills which if signed by the governor become law
